            "Charles Paul joined the section in January 2022 and was promoted to First Assistant Principal Bass in August 2023, succeeding Scott Haigh.[19][26] He holds the Mary E. and F. Joseph Callahan Chair.[26] A native of Detroit, he earned both bachelor\u2019s and master\u2019s degrees from Rice University\u2019s Shepherd School of Music, studying with Paul Ellison and Timothy Pitts.[26] He previously played in the Baltimore Symphony Orchestra.[26]",
