            "Pitts\u2019s students hold positions across this catalog. Charles Paul, Cleveland\u2019s current First Assistant Principal Bass, studied with him at Rice.[26] So did Daniel Gregory Smith, the associate principal bass of the San Francisco Symphony,[29] and Orion Miller, who joined the SFS section in 2024.[30] Caleb Quillen, the Boston Symphony Orchestra\u2019s current principal bass, studied with Pitts and Ellison at Rice before winning the BSO chair in 2025.[31] Brandon Mason, who joined Cleveland in July 2025, studied with Ellison at Rice.[37] Additional Pitts students hold positions in the Los Angeles Philharmonic, Houston Symphony, Detroit Symphony, National Symphony, Pittsburgh Symphony, and Atlanta Symphony.[32]",
