            "Mark Atherton, who joined in 1983 and is the longest-serving current member at forty-two years, studied at Boston University with Henry Portnoi, then principal bass of the Boston Symphony Orchestra.[33] He previously played in the Indianapolis Symphony Orchestra and the Boston Pops Esplanade Orchestra.[33] He plays an Italian bass by Tenoni and an American bass by Prescott.[33]",
            "Henry Peyrebrune joined in 1997, the same year as Dimoff, and holds the Charles Barr Memorial Chair.[34] He studied at the New England Conservatory with Edwin Barker, then principal bass of the BSO \u2014 making him the second member of the current section trained by a Boston principal.[34] Before Cleveland, he served as principal bass of the National Arts Centre Orchestra in Ottawa, the Portland Symphony, the Pro Arte Chamber Orchestra, and the Boston Philharmonic.[34] In 2014, he took on additional duties as a development gift officer in the orchestra\u2019s Philanthropy & Advancement office, a dual role he has maintained alongside his playing career.[34]",
