    bio: "Nathaniel West joined the Philadelphia Orchestra bass section in September 2017, a graduate of the Curtis Institute of Music where he studied with Harold Robinson and Edgar Meyer. A native of Columbus, Ohio, he was named a 2009 Presidential Scholar in the Arts — one of 20 recipients nationally and one of only four instrumentalists — and was a finalist in the National Foundation for the Advancement in the Arts YoungArts program, performing at the Kennedy Center in Washington, D.C., that year. He soloed with the New Albany Symphony and the Curtis Institute 20/21 ensemble.\n\nBefore joining Philadelphia he served as a member of the Kennedy Center Opera House Orchestra and performed in the bass sections of the Atlanta Symphony, East Coast Chamber Orchestra, San Antonio Symphony, and National Symphony. He has served as guest principal with the Atlanta and Toronto symphonies and the Festival Teatro del Lago Orchestra in Frutillar, Chile.\n\nAs a chamber musician, West performs regularly with the quintet Ensemble39 in Philadelphia and the Jupiter Chamber Players in New York, and spent three summers at the Marlboro Music Festival in Vermont. He has appeared at summer festivals including Twickenham Fest, the Vivo Music Festival in Columbus, the Luzerne Music Festival, and with the Chamber Music Society of Lincoln Center at its annual residency in Saratoga Springs. He is a member of the double bass faculty at Temple University's Boyer College of Music and Dance.",
